'''Tokyo Bijutsu Co., Ltd.''' (株式会社東京美術) is a Japanese publishing company based in {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京都|12=draft}} and part of the {{ill|Citizen Watch Group|ja|シチズン時計|12=draft}}.
== Overview == Established in [[1960]] (Showa 35), Tokyo Bijutsu is a publisher with a focus on art and archaeology. Its corporate logo, known as the "Leach Mark," was designed by renowned British ceramic artist {{ill|Bernard Leach|ja|バーナード・リーチ|12=draft}}.
The company also operates a media division, handling live broadcast subtitle production for news and information programs on {{ill|TV Asahi|ja|テレビ朝日|12=draft}} and {{ill|TV Tokyo|ja|テレビ東京|12=draft}}.
== History == * [[1960]] (Showa 35), March: Founded as a company for advertising, publishing, and printing. * [[1961]] (Showa 36): ** September: Began publishing and printing work for {{ill|Tokyo National Museum|ja|東京国立博物館|12=draft}}; started printing and sales promotion services for Citizen Watch. ** October: Began subtitling operations for NET (now TV Asahi). * [[1963]] (Showa 38), May: Established offset printing division. * [[1965]] (Showa 40), August: Established offset platemaking division. * [[1976]] (Showa 51), April: Spun off the offset platemaking division to form Tokyo Process Co., Ltd. * [[1980]] (Showa 55), December: Reached 300 major clients. * [[1987]] (Showa 62), March: Spun off the typesetting division to form Tokyo Bijutsu Typesetting Co., Ltd. * [[1990]] (Heisei 2), April: Renamed Tokyo Bijutsu Typesetting Co., Ltd. to Artword Tokyo. * [[1991]] (Heisei 3), March: Became a subsidiary of Citizen Shoji. * [[1992]] (Heisei 4), March: Spun off the offset printing division to establish Tobisei Center Co., Ltd. * [[1997]] (Heisei 9), November: Established digital animation training center. * [[2000]] (Heisei 12): ** February: Absorbed Tobisei Center Co., Ltd., renaming the division Offset Department of the Printing Division. ** June: Began printing operations in China, based in Hong Kong. * [[2003]] (Heisei 15), September: Opened Hong Kong office. * [[2004]] (Heisei 16): ** April: Became a subsidiary of Citizen Watch Co., Ltd. ** September: Renewed video production center. * [[2005]] (Heisei 17): ** January: Established CSR committee. ** May: Renovated headquarters building. * [[2007]] (Heisei 19), May: Acquired Privacy Mark certification. * [[2010]] (Heisei 22), March: Celebrated its 50th anniversary.
== Key Publications == * "Easy to Understand" Series ** [http://www.tokyo-bijutsu.co.jp/catalog/series/index.html View Tokyo Bijutsu's Easy to Understand Series] * "Want to Know More" Series * Archaeology Series ** Examples include works on prehistoric, Jomon, Yayoi, and Kofun periods, as well as environmental studies and artifact analysis.
== Financials (2024) == * Capital: ¥35 million * Net Income: ¥160,115,000 * Total Assets: ¥4,389,385,000 * Employees: 193 (as of May 31, 2021) == See Also == * {{ill|List of Japanese Publishing Companies|ja|日本の出版社一覧|12=draft}}
